(1164, 'blocks', 49, 'source', 'Update', '&lt;section id=&quot;blog_detail2&quot; class=&quot;row-builder js-dynamic-menu&quot; menu-name=&quot;blog_detail&quot;&gt;\r\n		&lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;div class=&quot;col-main&quot;&gt;\r\n				&lt;p class=&quot;topic&quot;&gt;Technology Category&lt;/p&gt;\r\n                &lt;p class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Mobile App Development Technology Blog&lt;/p&gt;\r\n 				&lt;img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/Untitled-1.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot; /&gt;\r\n 				&lt;div class=&quot;blog-detail-share&quot;&gt;\r\n                    &lt;strong&gt;SHARE:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\n                    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/twitter.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n                    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/face.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n                    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/gg.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n                    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/p.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n                    &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/in.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n                &lt;/div&gt;\r\n                &lt;div class=&quot;blog-detail-content&quot;&gt;Another important factor to consider when designing a retail app is how the user will physiologically use the app. Designing your app to ergonomically fit the hands of your user is crucial. If the app design layout makes it uncomfortable for the user, they’ll most likely get irritated which will reflect negatively on the brand and deviate from your overall goal.\r\n\r\n    A good blog can be a lifesaver for a developer. Some provide good background reading on the industry being worked on. Some provide code help, hints and tips, and other practical resources, while others just provide a well-earned distraction, which can be vital on a complex or challenging project. Here at Infragistics we provide lots of tools and controls for mobile web and app development. As a result we like to think we know a thing or two when it comes to the mobile development blogosphere. So here are our five favorite mobile development blogs at the moment:&lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;\r\n                    &lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-6 col-xs-12&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/Untitled-2.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot; &gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n                    &lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-6 col-xs-12&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;assets/images/blocks/blogs/Untitled-3.png&quot; alt=&quot;cannotload&quot; &gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n                &lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Aliquam laoreet turpis et neque elementum, quis condimentum justo porttitor. Nulla sed nunc ipsum. Quisque pellentesque vel mi et sodales. In id efficitur mi, eget venenatis purus. Curabitur vulputate urna lacus, in semper nisi tincidunt id. Morbi dapibus tellus id justo tincidunt, a suscipit ex pharetra. Sed commodo lectus eu facilisis suscipit. Sed finibus nec sem et dapibus. Sed scelerisque massa a urna scelerisque, ac condimentum velit venenatis.\r\n                &lt;strong&gt;John Doe - CEO&lt;/strong&gt;\r\n                &lt;/blockquote&gt;Another important factor to consider when designing a retail app is how the user will physiologically use the app. Designing your app to ergonomically fit the hands of your user is crucial. If the app design layout makes it uncomfortable for the user, they’ll most likely get irritated which will reflect negatively on the brand and deviate from your overall goal.\r\n\r\n    A good blog can b